            <div>
                <opener>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>all y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> pacquets are here &amp; lay me under fresh
                    obligations. I only lament the want of Letters to the <placeName ref="pldb.xml#pl0586">Leadhills</placeName>. my best complim<hi rend="superscript">ts</hi> &amp; thanks to <persName ref="pe0017">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Clerk.</persName> let me beg more
                    Letters to the S. E end of <placeName ref="pldb.xml#pl0223">L.
                        Lomond</placeName> also to the east side to meet me at <placeName ref="pldb.xml#pl0229">Glasgow</placeName> the 7<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> or 8<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> of next month. I hope <persName ref="pe0023">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Stuart</persName> will
                    not disappoint me: &amp; a good free draughtsman got. excuse me for not
                    answering <persName ref="pe0017">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                        Clerkeâ€™s</persName> Letter. I am partly uncertain whether he is in town. my
                    best compliments to <persName ref="pe0020">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Oliphant.</persName>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>y<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> in much
                            haste</salute>
                    <signed>
                        <persName ref="pe0232">Tho.
                            Pennant</persName>
                    </signed>
                    <add place="margin">
                        <del rend="overstrike">8 43</del>
                    </add>
                </closer>


                <dateline>
                    <placeName ref="pldb.xml#pl0253">Carlisle</placeName> May 28<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1772.</dateline>
            </div>
        </body>
